<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<p>Start using Qwenta in under a minute. No sign-up, no email — just your wallet.</p>

<h2>1. Connect Your Wallet</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Visit <strong>qwenta.xyz</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Connect Wallet</strong></li>
  <li>Select your wallet — MetaMask, Phantom, Coinbase, or WalletConnect</li>
  <li>Sign the authentication message (no transaction, no gas fee)</li>
  <li>You're in the dashboard</li>
</ol>

<p>Your wallet address is your identity. Each wallet gets its own isolated data — watchlists, portfolios, and chat history are private to you.</p>

<h2>2. Explore the Dashboard</h2>

<p>Once connected, you have access to the full platform:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Chart</strong> — Live price charts with RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands, SMA/EMA overlays. Switch timeframes (1H, 4H, Daily, Weekly) and periods (1D to 2Y).</li>
  <li><strong>Watchlist</strong> — Track your favorite symbols with live prices, daily change, and personal notes.</li>
  <li><strong>Portfolio</strong> — Record trades, track positions with weighted average cost, and monitor real-time P&amp;L.</li>
  <li><strong>Screener</strong> — Filter the market by RSI, MACD, SMA crosses, price range, and more. Use built-in presets or create custom filters.</li>
  <li><strong>Compare</strong> — Overlay up to 6 symbols on a normalized return chart.</li>
  <li><strong>AI Analyst</strong> — Ask QwenAI about any symbol. It has full context of live market data and indicators.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Search for a Symbol</h2>

<p>Type any stock ticker in the search bar (e.g., <code>AAPL</code>, <code>TSLA</code>, <code>NVDA</code>). The dashboard will load full OHLCV data with all technical indicators.</p>

<h2>4. Use the AI Analyst</h2>

<p>The AI chat panel is on the right side of the dashboard. Ask questions like:</p>

<ul>
  <li>"What does the RSI say about AAPL right now?"</li>
  <li>"Is TSLA showing a MACD bullish crossover?"</li>
  <li>"Give me a risk assessment for NVDA"</li>
  <li>"Compare the momentum of MSFT vs GOOG"</li>
</ul>

<p>QwenAI has full access to the current symbol's live data — price, volume, RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands, SMA, and more.</p>

<h2>5. Build Your Watchlist</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the <strong>Watchlist</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Add symbols you want to track</li>
  <li>See live prices and daily changes at a glance</li>
  <li>Add notes to any symbol for your own reference</li>
</ol>

<h2>6. Track Your Portfolio</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the <strong>Portfolio</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Add positions with buy price and quantity</li>
  <li>Track unrealized P&amp;L in real-time</li>
  <li>Record buy/sell transactions with fees</li>
</ol>

<h2>7. Export Data</h2>

<p>Export any symbol's full data (OHLCV + all indicators) as <strong>CSV</strong> or <strong>XLSX</strong> for external analysis.</p>

